headline: Exploring High Growth Tech Stocks In The US Market
summary: In the last week, the United States market has been flat, but over the past 12 months, it has risen by 14%, with earnings forecasted to grow by 15% annually. In this environment, identifying high growth tech stocks involves looking for companies with strong innovation potential and robust business models that can capitalize on these positive market conditions.

headline: Is CrowdStrike a Buy a Year After the Big IT Outage?
summary: CrowdStrike still is feeling the financial impact of the outage, but the company has continued to grow revenue and has kept customers loyal.  CrowdStrike (NASDAQ: CRWD) experienced the worst of times just one year ago.  At the time, insurers estimated it would cost U.S. Fortune 500 companies more than $5 billion, and over the past year, it's weighed on CrowdStrike's earnings too.
